Colossus (Spirit Temple).text: This Gossip Stone Is Dedicated to Those Who Perished Before Ganon Was Defeated.

DMC (Bombable Wall).text: I wanna be a rocketship, @! Please help me live my dreams!

DMC (Upper Grotto).text: When ASM is used to code a randomizer they should call it ASMR.

DMT (Biggoron).text: Did you know that the Boomerang instantly stuns Phantom Ganon's second form?

Dodongos Cavern (Bombable Wall).text: They say Ganon's tail is vulnerable to nuts, arrows, swords, explosives, hammers...^...sticks, seeds, boomerangs...^...rods, shovels, iron balls, angry bees...

GC (Medigoron).text: Where did Anju meet her lover?^${12 39 C7}At a Kafei.

GV (Waterfall).text: They say that the path to Termina is a one-way trip.

Graveyard (Shadow Temple).text: You found a spiritual Stone! By which I mean, I worship Nayru.

HC (Malon).text: They say that tossing a bomb will cause a Blue Bubble to go after it.

HC (Rock Wall).text: Have you ever tried hammering the ground or wall in a room with Torch Slugs, Flare Dancers, Tektites, Walltulas, Scrubs or Deku Babas?

HC (Storms Grotto).text: Did you know that there's a 1/201 chance per Rupee that the Zora from the diving minigame tosses a 500 Rupee?^Keep winning and the odds go up!

HF (Cow Grotto).text: Expired Spoiler Log? Don't worry! The OoTR Discord staff can help you out.

HF (Near Market Grotto).text: They say that Lon Lon Ranch prospered under Ingo.

HF (Open Grotto).text: Having trouble breathing underwater?^Have you tried wearing more BLUE?

HF (Southeast Grotto).text: Next you'll say:^"Why am I still reading these?"

KF (Deku Tree Left).text: Anything not saved will be lost.

KF (Deku Tree Right).text: They say that the real Phantom Ganon is bright and loud.

KF (Outside Storms).text: Did you know that you can access the Fire Temple boss door without dropping the pillar by using the Hover boots?

KF (Storms Grotto).text: Don't forget to write down your hints :)

Kak (Open Grotto).text: They say that if you don't use your slingshot at all when you play the slingshot minigame, the owner gets upset with you.

LH (Lab).text: @ tries to read the Gossip Stone...^${12 48 06}but he's standing on the wrong side of it!

LW (Bridge).text: They say that Ganondorf will appear in the next Mario Tennis.

LW (Near Shortcuts Grotto).text: Never give up. Trust your instincts!

SFM (Maze Lower).text: They say that Zelda's Lullaby can be used to repair broken signs.

SFM (Maze Upper).text: They say only one heart piece in all of Hyrule will declare the holder a winner.

SFM (Saria).text: Have you seen my dodongo? Very large, eats everything, responds to "King".^Call Darunia in Goron City if found. Huge rupee reward!

ToT (Left).text: Are you sure you want to play this? Wanna go get some tacos or something?

ToT (Left-Center).text: Three things are certain: death, taxes, and forgetting a check.

ToT (Right).text: Gossip Stone Shuffle must be on. I'm normally in Zora's Domain!

ToT (Right-Center).text: Dodongo's Cavern is much easier and faster to clear as Adult.

ZD (Mweep).text: Remember that time you did that really embarrassing thing?^${12 68 3A}Yikes.

ZF (Fairy).text: What is a Hylian? A miserable little pile of secrets!

ZF (Jabu).text: Try holding a D-pad button on the item screen.

ZR (Near Domain).text: They say that quest guidance can be found at a talking rock.

ZR (Near Grottos).text: This isn't where I parked my horse!

ZR (Open Grotto).text: Why are they called Wallmasters if they come from the ceiling?
